To view your Bench test results, you can run the bench UI locally by setting the BENCH_FILE_DIR environment variable to point to the location of your test runs and then running the 'bench' command from the command line. This will launch a local server that you can access via a URL in your browser.

Test suites in Bench are the main touch point for creating and running tests, while test runs are the actual execution of those tests within the test suite. Test suites define the data and parameters for the tests, while test runs execute those tests with specific inputs and outputs.
